		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Sybil Smith</span></strong> lives in Vermont and works as a nurse in the Vermont jails, which is not as scary as it may sound. She was a finalist in <em>Night Train</em>&rsquo;s summer 2002 Fifty-Fifty Fiction Award. Her essay in this issue is adapted from an unpublished book titled <em>My Mother&rsquo;s Early Lovers</em>. In 1996, the manuscript was made into a movie that won prizes at the Yale Film Festival and the Maine International Film Festival. She is currently in search of a publisher.</p><a href="/contributors/sybil-smith" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
